00:00:02,814 --> 00:00:05,151
No, no, no.

2
00:00:05,957 --> 00:00:07,649
Sorry, Ron, doors
are locked.

3
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,914
We've taken your key cards
and your phones,

4
00:00:09,921 --> 00:00:13,461
and the automatic timer won't go
off until tomorrow at 8:00 a.m.

5
00:00:13,484 --> 00:00:14,515
You're trapped in there.

6
00:00:14,535 --> 00:00:18,042
We told security not to disturb
you under any circumstances.

7
00:00:18,050 --> 00:00:20,305
And the phones and internet?
Oh, they've been disconnected.

8
00:00:20,330 --> 00:00:22,866
And I left a rusty
hacksaw on the table,

9
00:00:22,881 --> 00:00:25,514
so the first person who hacks
their face off gets release.

10
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:27,873
That's not—what?
Is that true?

11
00:00:27,889 --> 00:00:30,701
Guys, this is insane, okay?
Let us out.

12
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,921
Oh, my God, babe.
Game of Thrones is on tonight.

13
00:00:32,937 --> 00:00:34,229
It's the series finale.

14
00:00:34,251 --> 00:00:36,799
Khaleesi is marrying
Jack Sparrow.

15
00:00:36,814 --> 00:00:38,928
Oh, God, that show has really
gone off the rails.

16
00:00:38,951 --> 00:00:40,795
It makes sense
if you've read the books.

17
00:00:40,806 --> 00:00:43,056
Look, our baby monitor
is on the table.

18
00:00:43,071 --> 00:00:47,525
If you guys can talk this out and settle
your differences like grown-ups,

19
00:00:47,546 --> 00:00:50,338
turn it on, and I will come
to get you from my office.

20
00:00:50,363 --> 00:00:53,855
Otherwise, we will see you
at 8:00 a.m. tomorrow morning.

21
00:00:53,871 --> 00:00:57,806
I am going to break out of here,
then I am going to snap you in half.

22
00:00:57,822 --> 00:00:59,085
Hey.

23
00:00:59,110 --> 00:01:00,842
This is not his fault, Swanson.

24
00:01:00,849 --> 00:01:03,292
Be a man,
and get your house in order.

25
00:01:03,317 --> 00:01:04,785
You too, Knope.

26
00:01:05,348 --> 00:01:08,065
Good luck, you guys. I really hope
you can work out your differences.

27
00:01:08,079 --> 00:01:10,458
Terry, look at me.

28
00:01:10,483 --> 00:01:12,569
Is this what you
want to do?

29
00:01:12,591 --> 00:01:14,899
Think very carefully, son.

30
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:17,350
There you go.

31
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:18,786
That's right, buddy.

32
00:01:18,810 --> 00:01:20,248
Come on.

33
00:01:20,263 --> 00:01:23,039
For once in your life,
do something right.

34
00:01:23,048 --> 00:01:24,650
Stop it, Terry.

35
00:01:24,668 --> 00:01:26,148
Both of you.
Come on.

36
00:01:26,171 --> 00:01:27,684
Damn it, Terry!

37
00:01:39,786 --> 00:01:47,786
